======================================================================
ANALYSIS 1: n=5 FULL DIRECTED CYCLE + DISJOINTNESS
======================================================================

n=5: alpha_2 = 0 always (no room for disjoint cycles)
So H = 1 + 2*alpha_1 = 1 + 2*(c3_dir + c5_dir)

  Score (0, 1, 2, 3, 4): H=[1], c3=[0], c5=[0], alpha_1=[0], H=1+2*a1? True
  Score (0, 1, 3, 3, 3): H=[3], c3=[1], c5=[0], alpha_1=[1], H=1+2*a1? True
  Score (0, 2, 2, 2, 4): H=[3], c3=[1], c5=[0], alpha_1=[1], H=1+2*a1? True
  Score (0, 2, 2, 3, 3): H=[5], c3=[2], c5=[0], alpha_1=[2], H=1+2*a1? True
  Score (1, 1, 1, 3, 4): H=[3], c3=[1], c5=[0], alpha_1=[1], H=1+2*a1? True
  Score (1, 1, 2, 2, 4): H=[5], c3=[2], c5=[0], alpha_1=[2], H=1+2*a1? True
  Score (1, 1, 2, 3, 3): H=[9], c3=[3], c5=[1], alpha_1=[4], H=1+2*a1? True
  Score (1, 2, 2, 2, 3): H=[11, 13, 15], c3=[4], c5=[1, 2, 3], alpha_1=[5, 6, 7], H=1+2*a1? True
  Score (2, 2, 2, 2, 2): H=[15], c3=[5], c5=[2], alpha_1=[7], H=1+2*a1? True

======================================================================
ANALYSIS 2: n=6 FULL DIRECTED CYCLE + DISJOINTNESS
======================================================================

n=6: 3+3=6=n, so disjoint 3-3 pairs become possible!
But 3+5=8 > 6 and 5+5=10 > 6, so only 3-3 disjoint pairs exist.

H = 1 + 2*alpha_1 + 4*alpha_2 for all n=6 tournaments? True

Constraint analysis: c5_dir + k*alpha_2 = const?
